Reproduceable crash with switch statement
When attempting to compile the following code with default options (-jar compiler.jar --js filename) always produces the same error.    function a(b) {    switch (b.v) {      case 'SWITCH':        if (b.i >= 0) {          return b.o;        } else {          return undefined;        }        break;    }  }    Whenever I try and compile the above script I get a RuntimeException thrown:    INTERNAL COMPILER ERROR.  Please report this problem.  null    Node(BREAK): C:\test.js:11:3        break;    Parent: NULL    The result of calling --version on compiler.jar:    Version: 20100917 (revision 440)  Built on: 2010/09/17 17:55    The result of calling -version on java.exe:    java version "1.6.0_11"  Java(TM) SE Runtime Environment (build 1.6.0_11-b03)  Java HotSpot(TM) Client VM (build 11.0-b16, mixed mode, sharing)    Anyone else with the same issue - to work around in the short term, comment out the "break;" line.